[
    {
        "content": "<p>with the current design of field projections, this is an example of how I could imagine Rcu to look like in the end. <a href=\"https://github.com/BennoLossin/field-projections-designs/blob/main/02-handles/examples/RfL/rcu_example.rs\">https://github.com/BennoLossin/field-projections-designs/blob/main/02-handles/examples/RfL/rcu_example.rs</a></p>\n<p>Here's the example simplified a bit more:</p>",
        "id": 601405884,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1781006000
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We have the following structs:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Driver</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">driver_data</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Arc</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Mutex</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">DriverData</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">DriverData</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">shared</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Shared</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Shared</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Rcu</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Data</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Data</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">num</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 601405902,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1781006006
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And then these accessor functions:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Driver</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\">// Writing is easy and doesn't need field projections.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">write_data</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">new_data</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Data</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">guard</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">MutexGuard</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"nb\">_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">DriverData</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">driver_data</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">lock</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Rcu</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Data</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">pin</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">driver_data</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">shared</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">old</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">RcuOld</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Data</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">new_data</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">drop</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">old</span><span class=\"p\">);</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">// runs `synchronize_rcu` &amp; drops the old value</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\">// Reading needs field projections:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">read_data</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">guard</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">RcuGuard</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">read_lock</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">shared</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">InsideOfMutex</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Shared</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">driver_data</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">shared</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">InsideOfMutex</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Rcu</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Data</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">shared</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">Data</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">read</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">guard</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">num</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\">// Note that this can also be expressed succinctly:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">read_data</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">guard</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">RcuGuard</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">read_lock</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">shared</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">read</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">guard</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">num</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(note that this is written with pinning, but should work even nicer if we use the <code>Move</code> trait instead)</p>\n<p>I'd be interested in what people think, especially <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"411647\">@Boqun Feng</span>, <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"413824\">@Gary Guo</span>, <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"519727\">@Alice Ryhl</span> , <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"671004\">@Danilo Krummrich</span> and <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"411477\">@Miguel Ojeda</span> :)</p>",
        "id": 601405923,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1781006011
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the example on github compiles and shows a desugaring of the field projection design, it also shows as to what we would need to add to the kernel in order to make this work. in particular, this works for any lock types that we want Rcu to support, we just need to provide the equivalent of <code>InsideOfMutex</code> for them</p>",
        "id": 601406207,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1781006086
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Very cool!</p>",
        "id": 601415491,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1781008343
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think <a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/std/pin/struct.Pin.html#method.set\"><code>Pin::set</code></a> is a problem for the <code>Rcu</code> container.</p>",
        "id": 601421363,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1781009719
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess even with <code>!Move</code>, the direct assignment would be an issue?</p>",
        "id": 601422199,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1781009904
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes</p>",
        "id": 601422585,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1781009991
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"519727\">Alice Ryhl</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/field.20projections.20and.20Rcu/near/601421363\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I think <a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/std/pin/struct.Pin.html#method.set\"><code>Pin::set</code></a> is a problem for the <code>Rcu</code> container.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>but <code>Pin::set</code> require <code>Ptr</code> being <code>DerefMut</code>, which <code>Rcu</code> should not be. Assuming we are talking about <code>Pin&lt;Rcu&lt;Box&lt;..&gt;&gt;</code>.</p>",
        "id": 601422884,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1781010043
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm talking about the <code>Pin&lt;&amp;mut Rcu&lt;Box&lt;Data&gt;&gt;&gt;</code> which you created in <code>write_data</code>.</p>",
        "id": 601423167,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1781010102
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I see</p>",
        "id": 601423692,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1781010215
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>&amp;AtomicCell&lt;Pin&lt;&amp;mut Rcu&lt;Box&lt;Data&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;</code> might solve this?</p>",
        "id": 601429973,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1781011645
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>How? the issue is that pin projection gives you <code>Pin&lt;&amp;mut&gt;</code></p>",
        "id": 601431157,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1781011872
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>the example on github compiles and shows a desugaring of the field projection design, it also shows as to what we would need to add to the kernel in order to make this work.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So <code>adt_reflect!</code> and <code>field_of!</code> etc. is the desugaring, i.e. we wouldn't have to write that?</p>",
        "id": 601431303,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1781011903
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I meant pin projection should give a atomic pinned pointer instead.</p>",
        "id": 601431348,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1781011911
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I meant pin projection should give a atomic pinned pointer instead.</p>",
        "id": 601431369,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1781011914
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That would require <code>#[pin_data]</code> macro to know the type, which it couldn't</p>",
        "id": 601431477,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1781011944
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"519727\">Alice Ryhl</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/field.20projections.20and.20Rcu/near/601421363\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I think <a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/std/pin/struct.Pin.html#method.set\"><code>Pin::set</code></a> is a problem for the <code>Rcu</code> container.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Actually is <code>Pin::set</code> an issue if the type is not value-constructible (and only pin-constructible)?</p>",
        "id": 601431558,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1781011964
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Then you cannot call <code>Pin::set</code> as you don't have a value to begin with</p>",
        "id": 601431609,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1781011977
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but contructing a <code>Rcu&lt;Box&lt;Data&gt;&gt;</code> is what you need to do an update in general.</p>",
        "id": 601431835,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1781012026
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>what's why we need a <code>write()</code> function.</p>",
        "id": 601432069,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1781012078
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It should be <code>Box&lt;Data&gt;</code> that you're constructing and set with methods on <code>Rcu</code>?</p>",
        "id": 601432089,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1781012084
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would imagine that we have an analogy to <code>Pin::set</code> that works with <code>impl PinInit</code>.</p>",
        "id": 601432110,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1781012089
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"413824\">Gary Guo</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/field.20projections.20and.20Rcu/near/601432089\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It should be <code>Box&lt;Data&gt;</code> that you're constructing and set with methods on <code>Rcu</code>?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Oh, yes.</p>",
        "id": 601432385,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1781012149
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"519727\">Alice Ryhl</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/field.20projections.20and.20Rcu/near/601432110\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I would imagine that we have an analogy to <code>Pin::set</code> that works with <code>impl PinInit</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>pin-init does have it currently, but I guess the analogy with placing function is just <code>*mut_ref = placing_fn();</code></p>",
        "id": 601432661,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1781012211
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"546447\">@Benno Lossin</span> btw, <code>Rcu::write()</code> don't need to be <code>swap()</code>. it can be just <code>load()</code> and <code>store()</code>.</p>",
        "id": 601432732,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1781012225
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"519727\">Alice Ryhl</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/field.20projections.20and.20Rcu/near/601421363\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I think <a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/std/pin/struct.Pin.html#method.set\"><code>Pin::set</code></a> is a problem for the <code>Rcu</code> container.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>oh yeah, I had noticed that at some point too. I thought of the same solution as Gary in this thread:</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"413824\">Gary Guo</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/field.20projections.20and.20Rcu/near/601431558\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"519727\">Alice Ryhl</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/field.20projections.20and.20Rcu/near/601421363\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I think <a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/std/pin/struct.Pin.html#method.set\"><code>Pin::set</code></a> is a problem for the <code>Rcu</code> container.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Actually is <code>Pin::set</code> an issue if the type is not value-constructible (and only pin-constructible)?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>And then I also thought of:</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"413824\">Gary Guo</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/field.20projections.20and.20Rcu/near/601432661\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"519727\">Alice Ryhl</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/field.20projections.20and.20Rcu/near/601432110\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I would imagine that we have an analogy to <code>Pin::set</code> that works with <code>impl PinInit</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>pin-init does have it currently, but I guess the analogy with placing function is just <code>*mut_ref = placing_fn();</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So we probably need the <code>Overwrite</code> trait, or some other pointer wrapper that doesn't allow outright replacing the pointer, but does allow writing the pointee.</p>",
        "id": 601459650,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1781017671
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But since that's essentially just a more restrictive version of <code>Pin</code>, I'm sure we'll make it work</p>",
        "id": 601459767,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1781017697
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I could already change the example to show how it would work, but I suppose the projection is going to be a bit of pain...</p>",
        "id": 601459884,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1781017724
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411477\">Miguel Ojeda</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/field.20projections.20and.20Rcu/near/601431303\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>the example on github compiles and shows a desugaring of the field projection design, it also shows as to what we would need to add to the kernel in order to make this work.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So <code>adt_reflect!</code> and <code>field_of!</code> etc. is the desugaring, i.e. we wouldn't have to write that?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>yes, the <code>adt_reflect</code> macro would not be required, as that's going to be done with FRTs (which don't have enum support, which is why I created the macro)</p>",
        "id": 601460205,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1781017794
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411647\">Boqun Feng</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/field.20projections.20and.20Rcu/near/601432732\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"546447\">Benno Lossin</span> btw, <code>Rcu::write()</code> don't need to be <code>swap()</code>. it can be just <code>load()</code> and <code>store()</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>ahh right that's correct, I'll fix that :)</p>",
        "id": 601460285,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1781017808
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is this <code>adt_reflect!</code> macro something we can use in kernel right away?</p>",
        "id": 601469340,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1781019719
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>not sure what you want to use it for, I plan to never have it in the actual compiler implementation, this is just for the local examples</p>",
        "id": 601493072,
